body:
Does this issue occur when all extensions are disabled?: Yes

VS Code Version: 1.102.3 (Universal)
OS Version: macOS 15.5


## Error

When an extension is loaded with `--extensionDevelopmentPath` pointing to a subdirectory containing the manifest file instead of the extension root directory, `registerMcpServerDefinitionProvider` fails to find the declared MCP providers.

```
Error: MCP configuration providers must be registered in the contributes.mcpServerDefinitionProviders array within your package.json, but "my-mcp-provider" was not
```


## Configuration

**Launch Configuration:** (`.vscode/launch.json`)
```json
{
  "args": ["--extensionDevelopmentPath=${workspaceFolder}/src/templates"]
}
```

**Manifest file:**  (`templates/package.json`)
```json
{
  "contributes": {
    "mcpServerDefinitionProviders": [
      {
        "id": "my-mcp-provider",
        "label": "My MCP Provider"
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

## Code

```typescript
vscode.lm.registerMcpServerDefinitionProvider('my-mcp-provider', {
  provideMcpServerDefinitions: async () => { /* ... */ }
});
```

The registration fails despite the provider being correctly defined in `package.json` `contributes` section.


### Steps to Reproduce:

1. Clone the repo: https://github.com/rishavbharti/mcp-ext and install dependencies (`pnpm install`)
2. Add a breakpoint in the catch block in `extension.ts`
3. Run the extension and the debugger will hit the breakpoint showing the validation error
